0-12:00 (2 hours)\\n- **Afternoon**: 14:00-17:00 (3 hours)\\n- **Evening**: 19:00-22:00 (3 hours)\\n- **Activities**: Outdoor sports, friend gatherings, deep reading\\n\\n## Goals and Expectations\\n- Watch 4 new movies per month\\n- Complete 1 technical book per quarter\\n- Exercise 3 times per week\\n- Participate in 1 social activity per month\\n- Establish healthy entertainment-life balance\\n\\n---\\n/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_desktop_timeline_extraction_67580/travel_plan/travel_bucket_list.md:\\n# Travel Bucket List\\n\\n## Domestic Travel Destinations\\n\\n### Completed ✅\\n1. **Beijing** (2023)\\n   - Forbidden City, Great Wall, Temple of Heaven\\n   - Hutong cultural experience\\n   - Beijing Roast Duck, Zhajiangmian\\n\\n2. **Shanghai** (2023)\\n   - The Bund night view, Oriental Pearl Tower\\n   - Yu Garden, Tianzifang\\n   - Xiaolongbao, Shengjianbao\\n\\n3. **Chengdu** (2022)\\n   - Giant Panda Base, Kuanzhai Alley\\n   - Dujiangyan, Mount Qingcheng\\n   - Hotpot, Chuanchuanxiang\\n\\n### Planned 📅\\n1. **Xi'an** (April 2024)\\n   - Terracotta Warriors, Big Wild Goose Pagoda\\n   - Muslim Street, Bell and Drum Towers\\n   - Roujiamo, Yangrou Paomo\\n   - Budget: ¥3,000\\n\\n2. **Hangzhou** (June 2024)\\n   - West Lake, Lingyin Temple\\n   - Xixi Wetland, Thousand Island Lake\\n   - Longjing Tea, Dongpo Pork\\n   - Budget: ¥2,500\\n\\n3. **Qingdao** (August 2024)\\n   - Zhanqiao Pier, Badaguan\\n   - Mount Lao, Beer Museum\\n   - Seafood, Beer\\n   - Budget: ¥2,800\\n\\n### Future Plans 🔮\\n1. **Tibet** (2025)\\n   - Potala Palace, Jokhang Temple\\n   - Nam Co Lake, Mount Everest Base Camp\\n   - Chang (Barley Wine), Butter Tea\\n   - Budget: ¥8,000\\n\\n2. **Xinjiang** (2025)\\n   - Tianshan Mountains, Kanas Lake\\n   - Turpan, Grape Valley\\n   - Roasted Lamb, Hand-pulled Rice\\n   - Budget: ¥6,000\\n\\n## International Travel Destinations\\n\\n### Short-term Goals (1-2 years)\\n1. **Japan** 🇯🇵\\n   - Tokyo, Osaka, Kyoto\\n   - Mount Fuji, Nara Park\\n   - Sushi, Ramen, Tempura\\n   - Budget: ¥15,000\\n\\n2. **South Korea** 🇰🇷\\n   - Seoul, Busan, Jeju Island\\n   - Gyeongbokgung Palace, Haeundae\\n   - Korean BBQ, Kimchi, Fried Chicken\\n   - Budget: ¥8,000\\n\\n3. **Thailand** 🇹🇭\\n   - Bangkok, Chiang Mai, Phuket\\n   - Grand Palace, Wat Phra That Doi Suthep\\n   - Tom Yum Goong, Pad Thai\\n   - Budget: ¥6,000\\n\\n### Medium-term Goals (3-5 years)\\n1. **Europe** 🇪🇺\\n   - France, Italy, Germany\\n   - Eiffel Tower, Colosseum\\n   - Wine, Pasta, Beer\\n   - Budget: ¥30,000\\n\\n2. **United States** 🇺🇸\\n   - New York, Los Angeles, San Francisco\\n   - Statue of Liberty, Hollywood\\n   - Burgers, Hot Dogs, Pizza\\n   - Budget: ¥25,000\\n\\n3. **Australia** 🇦🇺\\n   - Sydney, Melbourne, Great Barrier Reef\\n   - Sydney Opera House, Great Ocean Road\\n   - Seafood, Steak, Wine\\n   - Budget: ¥20,000\\n\\n### Long-term Goals (5-10 years)\\n1. **Antarctica** 🇦🇶\\n   - Antarctic Peninsula, Penguin Island\\n   - Glaciers, Aurora\\n   - Polar Expedition Experience\\n   - Budget: ¥100,000\\n\\n2. **Africa** 🇿🇦\\n   - South Africa, Kenya, Egypt\\n   - Cape of Good Hope, Masai Mara\\n   - Wildlife, Pyramids\\n   - Budget: ¥50,000\\n\\n## Travel Preparation Checklist\\n\\n### Essential Items\\n- [ ] Passport/ID Card\\n- [ ] Credit Card/Cash\\n- [ ] Charger/Adapter\\n- [ ] Camera/Phone\\n- [ ] Common Medicines\\n- [ ] Travel Insurance\\n\\n### Skill Preparation\\n- [ ] English Speaking Practice\\n- [ ] Photography Skills Learning\\n- [ ] Local Culture Understanding\\n- [ ] Travel Guide Research\\n- [ ] Budget Planning Skills\\n\\n### Health Preparation\\n- [ ] Health Check Report\\n- [ ] Vaccination\\n- [ ] Altitude Adaptation Training\\n- [ ] Physical Training\\n- [ ] Emergency Response Knowledge\\n\\n## Travel Budget Planning\\n\\n### Annual Travel Budget\\n- **Domestic Travel**: ¥15,000\\n- **International Travel**: ¥50,000\\n- **Total**: ¥65,000\\n\\n### Savings Plan\\n- **Monthly Savings**: ¥5,500\\n- **Year-end Bonus**: ¥20,000\\n- **Investment Returns**: ¥10,000\\n\\n## Travel Recording Methods\\n- **Photos**: At least 3 photos per attraction\\n- **Videos**: Record important moments\\n- **Diary**: Daily feeling records\\n- **Maps**: Footprint marking\\n- **Souvenirs**: Collect unique items\\n\\n## Travel Goals\\n- Complete at least 2 domestic trips per year\\n- Complete 1 international trip every 2 years\\n- Complete major Asian countries before age 30\\n- Complete major European countries before age 40\\n- Complete all seven continents before age 50\\n\\n---\\n/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_desktop_timeline_extraction_67580/travel_plan/travel_calculator.py:\\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\\n# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nTravel Budget Calculator\\nUsed for calculating travel expenses and creating budget plans\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nimport json\\nimport datetime\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional\\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass TravelExpense:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Travel expense data class\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    category: str\\n    amount: float\\n    currency: str = \\\"CNY\\\"\\n    description: str = \\\"\\\"\\n    date: str = \\\"\\\"\\n\\nclass TravelBudgetCalculator:\\n    def __init__(self, budget_file: str = \\\"travel_budget.json\\\"):\\n        self.budget_file = Path(budget_file)\\n        self.budgets = self.load_budgets()\\n    \\n    def load_budgets(self) -> Dict:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Load budget data\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if self.budget_file.exists():\\n            try:\\n                with open(self.budget_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\\n                    return json.load(f)\\n            except json.JSONDecodeError:\\n                print(\\\"Budget file corrupted, creating new budget file\\\")\\n                return {\\\"trips\\\": [], \\\"expenses\\\": [], \\\"categories\\\": []}\\n        return {\\\"trips\\\": [], \\\"expenses\\\": [], \\\"categories\\\": []}\\n    \\n    def save_budgets(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Save budget data\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        with open(self.budget_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\\n            json.dump(self.budgets, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)\\n    \\n    def add_trip(self, destination: str, start_date: str, end_date: str, \\n                 total_budget: float, currency: str = \\\"CNY\\\"):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Add travel plan\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        trip = {\\n            \\\"id\\\": len(self.budgets[\\\"trips\\\"]) + 1,\\n            \\\"destination\\\": destination,\\n            \\\"start_date\\\": start_date,\\n            \\\"end_date\\\": end_date,\\n            \\\"total_budget\\\": total_budget,\\n            \\\"currency\\\": currency,\\n            \\\"created_date\\\": datetime.datetime.now().isoformat(),\\n            \\\"status\\\": \\\"Planning\\\"\\n        }\\n        \\n        self.budgets[\\\"trips\\\"].append(trip)\\n        self.save_budgets()\\n        print(f\\\"Travel plan '{destination}' has been added\\\")\\n    \\n    def add_expense(self, trip_id: int, category: str, amount: float, \\n                   description: str = \\\"\\\", currency: str = \\\"CNY\\\"):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Add travel expense\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        expense = TravelExpense(\\n            category=category,\\n            amount=amount,\\n            currency=currency,\\n            description=description,\\n            date=datetime.datetime.now().isoformat()\\n        )\\n        \\n        expense_dict = {\\n            \\\"id\\\": len(self.budgets[\\\"expenses\\\"]) + 1,\\n            \\\"trip_id\\\": trip_id,\\n            \\\"category\\\": expense.category,\\n            \\\"amount\\\": expense.amount,\\n            \\\"currency\\\": expense.currency,\\n            \\\"description\\\": expense.description,\\n            \\\"date\\\": expense.date\\n        }\\n        \\n        self.budgets[\\\"expenses\\\"].append(expense_dict)\\n        \\n        # Add new category\\n        if category not in self.budgets[\\\"categories\\\"]:\\n            self.budgets[\\\"categories\\\"].append(category)\\n        \\n        self.save_budgets()\\n        print(f\\\"Expense record added: {category} - {amount} {currency}\\\")\\n    \\n    def calculate_trip_expenses(self, trip_id: int) -> Dict:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Calculate total travel expenses\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        trip_expenses = [exp for exp in self.budgets[\\\"expenses\\\"] if exp[\\\"trip_id\\\"] == trip_id]\\n        \\n        if not trip_expenses:\\n            return {\\\"total\\\": 0, \\\"by_category\\\": {}, \\\"currency\\\": \\\"CNY\\\"}\\n        \\n        total = sum(exp[\\\"amount\\\"] for exp in trip_expenses)\\n        currency = trip_expenses[0][\\\"currency\\\"]\\n        \\n        # Statistics by category\\n        by_category = {}\\n        for exp in trip_expenses:\\n            cat = exp[\\\"category\\\"]\\n            if cat not in by_category:\\n                by_category[cat] = 0\\n            by_category[cat] += exp[\\\"amount\\\"]\\n        \\n        return {\\n            \\\"total\\\": total,\\n            \\\"by_category\\\": by_category,\\n            \\\"currency\\\": currency\\n        }\\n    \\n    def get_budget_status(self, trip_id: int) -> Dict:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Get budget status\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        trip = None\\n        for t in self.budgets[\\\"trips\\\"]:\\n            if t[\\\"id\\\"] == trip_id:\\n                trip = t\\n                break\\n        \\n        if not trip:\\n            return {\\\"error\\\": \\\"Travel plan does not exist\\\"}\\n        \\n        expenses = self.calculate_trip_expenses(trip_id)\\n        total_budget = trip[\\\"total_budget\\\"]\\n        total_expenses = expenses[\\\"total\\\"]\\n        \\n        remaining = total_budget - total_expenses\\n        percentage = (total_expenses / total_budget) * 100 if total_budget > 0 else 0\\n        \\n        return {\\n            \\\"destination\\\": trip[\\\"destination\\\"],\\n            \\\"total_budget\\\": total_budget,\\n            \\\"total_expenses\\\": total_expenses,\\n            \\\"remaining\\\": remaining,\\n            \\\"percentage_used\\\": percentage,\\n            \\\"status\\\": \\\"Over Budget\\\" if remaining < 0 else \\\"Normal\\\" if percentage < 80 else \\\"Near Budget\\\"\\n        }\\n    \\n    def get_expense_categories(self) -> List[str]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Get expense categories\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.budgets[\\\"categories\\\"]\\n    \\n    def export_trip_report(self, trip_id: int, filename: str = None):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Export travel report\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        trip = None\\n        for t in self.budgets[\\\"trips\\\"]:\\n            if t[\\\"id\\\"] == trip_id:\\n                trip = t\\n                break\\n        \\n        if not trip:\\n            print(\\\"Travel plan does not exist\\\")\\n            return\\n        \\n        expenses = self.calculate_trip_expenses(trip_id)\\n        budget_status = self.get_budget_status(trip_id)\\n        \\n        if not filename:\\n            filename = f\\\"trip_report_{trip['destination']}_{datetime.datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d')}.txt\\\"\\n        \\n        with open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\\n            f.write(f\\\"Travel Report: {trip['destination']}\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(\\\"=\\\" * 50 + \\\"\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"Travel Period: {trip['start_date']} to {trip['end_date']}\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"Total Budget: {trip['total_budget']} {trip['currency']}\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"Total Expenses: {expenses['total']} {expenses['currency']}\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"Remaining Budget: {budget_status['remaining']} {expenses['currency']}\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"Budget Usage: {budget_status['percentage_used']:.1f}%\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"Budget Status: {budget_status['status']}\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n            \\n            f.write(\\\"Expense Category Details:\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(\\\"-\\\" * 30 + \\\"\\\\n\\\")\\n            for category, amount in expenses[\\\"by_category\\\"].items():\\n                f.write(f\\\"{category}: {amount} {expenses['currency']}\\\\n\\\")\\n        \\n        print(f\\\"Travel report exported to: {filename}\\\")\\n\\ndef main():\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Main function example\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    calculator = TravelBudgetCalculator()\\n    \\n    # Add travel plan\\n    calculator.add_trip(\\\"Hong Kong\\\", \\\"2024-03-15\\\", \\\"2024-03-20\\\", 5000)\\n    \\n    # Add expense records\\n    calculator.add_expense(1, \\\"Transportation\\\", 1500, \\\"Round-trip airfare\\\")\\n    calculator.add_expense(1, \\\"Accommodation\\\", 800, \\\"Hotel fees\\\")\\n    calculator.add_expense(1, \\\"Food\\\", 500, \\\"Daily meals\\\")\\n    \\n    # Check budget status\\n    status = calculator.get_budget_status(1)\\n    print(f\\\"Budget Status: {status}\\\")\\n    \\n    # Export report\\n    calculator.export_trip_report(1)\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    main()\\n\", \"annotations\": null, \"meta\": null}], \"structuredContent\": {\"content\": \"/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_desktop_timeline_extraction_67580/exp_logs/aug/augmentation_log.txt:\\nData Augmentation Experiment Log\\n================================\\n\\nDate: 2024-01-15\\nExperimenter: Chen Lingjun\\n\\nExperiment Objective:\\n- Test the impact of different data augmentation techniques on model performance\\n- Compare training effectiveness between original and augmented data\\n\\nAugmentation Techniques Used:\\n1. Random Rotation (0-360 degrees)\\n2. Random Scaling (0.8-1.2x)\\n3. Random Flip (horizontal/vertical)\\n4. Noise Addition (Gaussian noise)\\n5. Brightness Adjustment (±20%)\\n\\nExperiment Results:\\n- Original data accuracy: 82.3%\\n- Augmented data accuracy: 87.1%\\n- Performance improvement: +4.8%\\n\\nConclusion:\\nData augmentation techniques significantly improve model generalization and robustness.\\nRecommend using augmented data for training in production environments.\\n\\nNext Steps:\\n- Test more augmentation technique combinations\\n- Analyze individual effects of different augmentation techniques\\n- Optimize augmentation parameters\\n\\n---\\n/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_desktop_timeline_extraction_67580/exp_logs/exp_record.md:\\n# Experiment Records\\n\\n## Project Overview\\n- Project Name: TBD\\n- Start Date: 2024\\n- Status: In Progress\\n\\n## Experiment Logs\\n### 2024-08-XX\\n- Experiment Content:\\n- Results:\\n- Notes:\\n\\n### 2024-09-XX\\n- Experiment Content:\\n- Results:\\n- Notes:\\n\\n## Next Steps\\n- [ ] Data Analysis\\n- [ ] Result Verification\\n- [ ] Report Writing\\n\\n---\\n/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_desktop_timeline_extraction_67580/exp_logs/experiment_summary.md:\\n# Experiment Log Summary\\n\\n## Project Overview\\n\\n- **Project 1**: Machine Learning Model Training\\n- **Project 2**: Data Analysis Experiment\\n- **aug**: Data Augmentation Experiment\\n- **sep**: September Experiment Records\\n\\n## Recent Experiments\\n\\n- 2024-01-15: Completed preliminary testing for Project 1\\n- 2024-01-10: Started data augmentation experiment\\n- 2024-01-05: Completed data analysis for Project 2\\n\\n## Todo List\\n\\n- [ ] Optimize Project 1 model parameters\\n- [ ] Complete aug experiment report\\n- [ ] Organize sep experiment data\\n\\n\\n---\\n/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_desktop_timeline_extraction_67580/exp_logs/project_1/README.md:\\n# Project 1 - Machine Learning Model Training\\n\\n## Project Description\\n\\nThis is a machine learning model training project with the main goal of developing an efficient classification algorithm.\\n\\n## File Structure\\n\\n- `model.py`: Model definition\\n- `train.py`: Training script\\n- `data.csv`: Training data\\n- `results.txt`: Experiment results\\n\\n## Usage\\n\\n1. Prepare data\\n2. Run training script\\n3. Evaluate model performance\\n\\n## Experiment Results\\n\\n- Accuracy: 85.6%\\n- Training time: 2.5 hours\\n- Model size: 15.2MB\\n\\n\\n---\\n/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_desktop_timeline_extraction_67580/exp_logs/project_1/data.csv:\\nfeature1,feature2,feature3,feature4,feature5,target\\n1.2,3.4,5.6,7.8,9.0,0\\n2.1,4.3,6.5,8.7,10.9,1\\n3.0,5.2,7.4,9.6,11.8,0\\n4.1,6.3,8.5,10.7,12.9,1\\n5.2,7.4,9.6,11.8,13.0,0\\n6.3,8.5,10.7,12.9,14.1,1\\n7.4,9.6,11.8,13.0,15.2,0\\n8.5,10.7,12.9,14.1,16.3,1\\n9.6,11.8,13.0,15.2,17.4,0\\n10.7,12.9,14.1,16.3,18.5,1\\n\\n---\\n/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_desktop_timeline_extraction_67580/exp_logs/project_1/model.py:\\nimport numpy as np\\nimport pandas as pd\\nfrom sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\nfrom sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report\\n\\nclass MLModel:\\n    def __init__(self, n_estimators=100):\\n        self.model = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=n_estimators)\\n        self.is_trained = False\\n    \\n    def train(self, X, y):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Train the model\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.model.fit(X, y)\\n        self.is_trained = True\\n        print(\\\"Model training completed\\\")\\n    \\n    def predict(self, X):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Make predictions\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not self.is_trained:\\n            raise ValueError(\\\"Model not yet trained\\\")\\n        return self.model.predict(X)\\n    \\n    def evaluate(self, X_test, y_test):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Evaluate model performance\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        y_pred = self.predict(X_test)\\n        accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\\n        report = classification_report(y_test, y_pred)\\n        return accuracy, report\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    # Example usage\\n    model = MLModel()\\n    print(\\\"Machine learning model initialized successfully\\\")\\n\\n---\\n/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_desktop_timeline_extraction_67580/exp_logs/project_2/analysis_report.md:\\n# Project 2 - Data Analysis Report\\n\\n## Data Overview\\n- **Data Source**: User behavior logs\\n- **Data Volume**: 10,000 records\\n- **Time Range**: January 1-31, 2024\\n\\n## Key Findings\\n1. User activity peaks on weekends\\n2. Mobile usage accounts for 65%\\n3. Most popular feature is search functionality\\n\\n## Data Quality\\n- Completeness: 98.5%\\n- Accuracy: 96.2%\\n- Consistency: 94.8%\\n\\n## Recommendations\\n- Optimize mobile user experience\\n- Improve search functionality relevance\\n- Enhance server performance on weekends\\n\\n---\\n/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_desktop_timeline_extraction_67580/exp_logs/project_2/data_analysis.py:\\nimport pandas as pd\\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\nimport seaborn as sns\\nfrom datetime import datetime\\n\\ndef load_data(file_path):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Load data\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    return pd.read_csv(file_path)\\n\\ndef analyze_user_behavior(data):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Analyze user behavior\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Basic statistics\\n    print(\\\"Data basic information:\\\")\\n    print(data.info())\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nData statistical summary:\\\")\\n    print(data.describe())\\n    \\n    # Time analysis\\n    if 'timestamp' in data.columns:\\n        data['timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(data['timestamp'])\\n        data['hour'] = data['timestamp'].dt.hour\\n        data['day_of_week'] = data['timestamp'].dt.dayofweek\\n        \\n        # Statistics by hour\\n        hourly_stats = data.groupby('hour').size()\\n        print(\\\"\\\\nStatistics by hour:\\\")\\n        print(hourly_stats)\\n    \\n    return data\\n\\ndef generate_visualizations(data):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Generate visualization charts\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))\\n    \\n    # Example chart\\n    plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)\\n    plt.title(\\\"Data Distribution\\\")\\n    plt.hist(data.iloc[:, 0], bins=20)\\n    \\n    plt.tight_layout()\\n    plt.show()\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    print(\\\"Data analysis script started\\\")\\n    # Add specific data file path here\\n\\n---\\n/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_desktop_timeline_extraction_67580/exp_logs/results_record.csv:\\nDate,Experiment_ID,Temperature,Humidity,Result,Notes\\n2024-08-01,EXP001,25.5,60%,Success,Initial Test\\n2024-08-02,EXP002,26.0,58%,Success,Repeated Verification\\n2024-08-03,EXP003,24.8,62%,Failed,Parameter Adjustment\\n2024-08-04,EXP004,25.2,59%,Success,Optimized Test\\n\\n---\\n/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_desktop_timeline_extraction_67580/exp_logs/sep/september_summary.csv:\\ndate,experiment_type,status,results,notes\\n2024-09-01,Model Training,Completed,Accuracy 85.2%,Used new dataset\\n2024-09-05,Parameter Tuning,In Progress,Pending,Testing different learning rates\\n2024-09-10,Data Preprocessing,Completed,Data cleaning completed,Removed outliers\\n2024-09-15,Model Evaluation,Completed,F1 Score 0.87,Good performance\\n2024-09-20,Deployment Testing,In Progress,Pending,Testing production environment\\n2024-09-25,Documentation,Completed,README updated,Added usage instructions\\n2024-09-30,Project Summary,Pending,Pending,Organize experiment report\\n\\n---\\n/Users/mango/workspace/geode/artifacts/eval/harnesses/mcpmark/.mcpmark_backups/backup_filesystem_de